                    <span>I prefer Burton Watson's translation to Palmer and Breuilly's, especially after reading parts in the Chinese text. But Palmer and Breuilly won't steer U wrong though. No, this is a decent translation of the entire text, which is not a common sight! Only Burton Watson, James Legge, and Victor Mair have put out complete Zhuangzi translations. AC Graham's translation is also quite good.<p>BAO PU-<br>embrace simplicity</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Not good for a beginner</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
